        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="TK150">
<l>aṟaṉvaraiyā ṉalla ceyiṉum piṟaṉvaraiyāḷ</l>
<l>peṇmai nayavāmai naṉṟu</l>            
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Even if one who does not taken in<note place="foot">Tamil Lexicon gives "To make one's own, appropriate" as a meaning of வரைதல், but cites this kuṟaḷ (specifically Parmiēlaḻakar's commentary upon it) for that meaning. On analogy with how aṟaṉkaṭal niṉṟār is explained ad 142, one might might alternatively interpret that aṟaṉvaraiyāṉ here means "he who is outside of dharma's bound."</note> dharma does its opposite, it is good</l>
<l>that he not desire the womanhood of her taken in by another.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
